\end{frame}

\subsection{Software Tools for Semantic Web Programming} 
\begin{frame}




Many tools and methodologies exist for the construction of ontologies. Some potential candidates are listed below.These tools may be divided into two groups
\begin{enumerate}
	\item Tools for which the knowledge model is directly formalized in an ontology language:
\begin{itemize}
	\item Ontolingua Server
        \item OntoSaurus (Loom)
        \item OILed (OIL then DAML+OIL then OWL)
        \item Inference engines such as Fact and Racer
\end{itemize}
   \item Tools for which the knowledge model is independent from the ontology language:
\begin{itemize}
	\item Protege-OWL
        \item OntoEdit
        \item KAON
\end{itemize}
\end{enumerate}

\end{frame}
\subsection{APIs for Semantic Web Programming} 
\begin{frame}

\begin{itemize}
	\item Jena is a programmer's API (application programming interface) for Java semantic
web applications. 
\item Primary use of Jena is to  write Java code that handles
RDF and OWL documents and descriptions.
\item  In Jena, a graph is called a model and is represented by the Model interface
\item The Named Graphs API for Jena (NG4J) is an extension to the Jena Semantic Web framework for parsing, manipulating and serializing sets of Named Graphs.
\item Sindice is a platform to build applications on top of named graphs . Sindice collects Web Data in many ways, following existing web standards, and offers Search and Querying across this data, updated live every few minutes.
\ite Sinice API consists of the following APIs
\begin{itemize}
	 
\item Sindice Search API
\item Sindice Cache API
\item Sindice Live API
\item Sindice Ping Submission API
\item Sigma API
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}
\subsection{SPARQL Engine } 
\begin{frame}
\begin{itemize}

\item Joseki is a Web-based SPARQL endpoint.
\iten Joseki contains its own Web server, which hosts a Java servlet engine to support its SPARQL endpoint.
\item  It renders a Web query form so that user can enter the query manually, and by submitting the query form, it will return  the query result right away.
\end{itemize}
