\subsection{Domain Ontology: FOAF}
\begin{frame}
\begin{itemize}
	\item FOAF stands for Friend of a Friend
         \item FOAF is  a vocabulary (or, ontology) which includes the
basic terms to describe personal information, such as who you are, what you do,
and who your friends are.
\item It serves as a standard for everyone who wants to mark
up their home pages and turn them into the documents that can be processed by
machines.
\end{itemize}
  \begin{center}
	\includegraphics[scale=0.32]{foaffile.png}
	\captionof{figure}{FOAF file}
\end{center}


\end{frame}



