\section{Challenges and Obstacles}
\begin{frame}
\begin{itemize}
	\item This  work is designed to work on yet to emerge semantic web environment.
\item Most of the semantic web terminologies are in a premature stage and technologies
are yet to converge.
\item Most of the tools and APIs used are products of academic
research and difficult to integrate.
\item MVC architecture is not suitable for semantic web programming
\item In order to capture formal constraints, an additional constraint language  has to be used along with UML to incorporate semantic web concepts.
\item Technical issues such as scalability and usability.
\item Social issues (trust, privacy, etc.)
\item Economic issues (building a critical mass)
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\section{Conclusion}
\begin{frame}
\begin{itemize}
	\item The Semantic Web is big. It is fluid. It is dynamic and
evolving.
\item This paper summarizes the use of ontology in Web mining. 
\item  Through this work it is proved  that ontology was undoubtedly a key concept on Semantic Web and Semantic web mining  pathway.
\item The future Semantic Web development will depend on the progress of ontologies engineering.
\item Further investigating this interplay will give rise to new research
questions and stimulate further research both in the Semantic
Web and in Web Mining,towards the ultimate goal of
Semantic Web Mining: a better Web, for all of its users
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}





